  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Schwannomas are benign tumors that can reach giant sizes. The diagnosis and treatment of
      these cases differ from those of small schwannomas. The aim of this study was to review the
      diagnoses and surgical approach characteristics of the giant spinal schwannomas (GSS) of
      patients who underwent surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
